1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,440
2.

2
00:00:01,869 --> 00:00:04,640
Practice calling people by their names.

3
00:00:05,069 --> 00:00:15,278
Every year, shrewd manufacturers sell more briefcases, pencils, Bibles, and hundreds of other items just by putting the buyer's name on the product.

4
00:00:15,470 --> 00:00:17,680
People like to be called by name.

5
00:00:17,788 --> 00:00:21,038
It gives everyone a boost to be addressed by name.

6
00:00:21,710 --> 00:00:24,160
Two special things you must remember.

7
00:00:24,269 --> 00:00:27,599
Pronounce the name correctly and spell it correctly.

8
00:00:27,710 --> 00:00:34,480
If you mispronounce or misspell someone's name, that person feels that you feel he is unimportant.

9
00:00:35,069 --> 00:00:37,200
And here's one special reminder.

10
00:00:37,230 --> 00:00:41,359
When talking with people you don't know well, add the appropriate title,

11
00:00:41,470 --> 00:00:47,839
Miss, Mr. or Mrs. The office boy prefers Mr. Jones to just Jones.

12
00:00:47,950 --> 00:00:49,839
So does your junior assistant.

13
00:00:49,950 --> 00:00:51,920
So do people at every level.

14
00:00:52,028 --> 00:00:56,240
These little titles help tremendously to make people feel important.

15
00:00:56,269 --> 00:00:57,759
3.

16
00:00:57,950 --> 00:00:59,599
Don't hog glory.

17
00:00:59,629 --> 00:01:01,278
Invest it instead.

18
00:01:01,789 --> 00:01:05,759
Just recently I was a guest at an all-day sales convention.

19
00:01:05,869 --> 00:01:13,440
After dinner that evening, the vice president in charge of sales for the company passed out awards to the two district managers,

20
00:01:13,549 --> 00:01:19,680
a man and a woman, whose sales organizations had attained the best records for the year just ended.

21
00:01:19,950 --> 00:01:30,160
Then the vice president asked those district managers to take fifteen minutes to tell the entire group how their organizations did so exceptionally well.

22
00:01:30,829 --> 00:01:41,680
The first district manager, who I later learned had been appointed a manager only three months before and was therefore only partially responsible for his organization's record,

23
00:01:41,950 --> 00:01:44,799
got up and explained how he did it.

24
00:01:45,229 --> 00:01:51,278
He conveyed the impression that his efforts, and his efforts alone, caused the sales increase.

25
00:01:51,470 --> 00:01:56,160
Remarks such as, When I took over, I did such and such.

26
00:01:56,348 --> 00:01:59,359
Things were in a mess, but I cleared them up.

27
00:01:59,549 --> 00:02:06,479
It wasn't easy, but I just grabbed hold of the situation and wouldn't let go, characterized his talk.

28
00:02:06,990 --> 00:02:12,560
As he talked, I could see the increasing resentment gathering in the faces of his salesmen.

29
00:02:12,828 --> 00:02:17,600
They were being ignored for the sake of the district manager's personal glory.

30
00:02:17,868 --> 00:02:23,839
Their hard work, which was responsible for the sales increase, was completely unrecognized.

31
00:02:24,430 --> 00:02:32,080
Then the second district manager got up to make her short talk, but this lady used an entirely different approach.

32
00:02:32,269 --> 00:02:39,680
First, she explained that the reason for her organization's success was the wholehearted effort of her sales force.

33
00:02:39,950 --> 00:02:47,439
Then she asked each one to stand and paid a sincere personal compliment to each for his or her efforts.

34
00:02:48,028 --> 00:02:49,600
Note this difference.

35
00:02:49,788 --> 00:02:54,879
The first manager squandered the vice president's praise entirely on himself.

36
00:02:55,069 --> 00:02:57,919
In doing so, he offended his own people.

37
00:02:58,028 --> 00:03:00,479
His sales force was demoralized.

38
00:03:00,749 --> 00:03:06,080
The second passed the praise on to her sales force, where it could do more good.

39
00:03:06,348 --> 00:03:11,759
This manager knew that praise, like money, can be invested to pay dividends.

40
00:03:11,950 --> 00:03:18,080
She knew that passing the credit on to her sales people would make them work even harder next year.

41
00:03:18,509 --> 00:03:21,120
Remember, praise is power.

